<SEQUENCE TIMEOUT="" EXIT-ON="FAILURE">
  <COMMENT></COMMENT>
</SEQUENCE>

<SEQUENCE TIMEOUT="" EXIT-ON="FAILURE">
  <COMMENT> a stupid service to fix the nonsense with softwareag&#39;s ftp implementation - it deals with messages that can sometimes fail with </COMMENT>
</SEQUENCE>

<SEQUENCE TIMEOUT="" EXIT-ON="FAILURE">
  <COMMENT> a message looking like: com.wm.app.b2b.server.ServiceException:[ISC.0064.9005] 530 Login incorrect. </COMMENT>
</SEQUENCE>

<SEQUENCE TIMEOUT="" EXIT-ON="FAILURE">
  <COMMENT> and sometimes complete normally with an ftp failure like: 530 Login incorrect. </COMMENT>
</SEQUENCE>

<SEQUENCE TIMEOUT="" EXIT-ON="FAILURE">
  <COMMENT></COMMENT>
</SEQUENCE>

<SEQUENCE NAME="MAIN" TIMEOUT="" EXIT-ON="SUCCESS">
  <COMMENT></COMMENT>

  <!-- nodes -->

<SEQUENCE NAME="TRY" TIMEOUT="" EXIT-ON="FAILURE">
  <COMMENT></COMMENT>

  <!-- nodes -->

<MAP TIMEOUT="" MODE="STANDALONE">
  <COMMENT></COMMENT>
</MAP>

<INVOKE TIMEOUT="" SERVICE="pub.client.ftp:login" VALIDATE-IN="$none" VALIDATE-OUT="$none">
  <COMMENT> sHost sPort sUid sPwd sTimeout sEncoding sXferTypeActPsv </COMMENT>

